Defendant Kelvin D Davis in court, in custody from MHOC, with attorney Paul Craford for attorney Katie B. Kegel.   David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State presents the offer.  Atty. Crawford confirms the offer as placed on the record.  Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Court orders Count 1 dismissed and read in as well as case 17CM762 will be dismissed and read into this case.  State presents their recommendations for sentencing.  Atty. Crawford presents his recommendations for sentencing.  Defendant presents statements.  Defendant may be returned to Milwaukee House of Corrections forthwith, but per the order below be returned to Waukesha Co. to serve out this sentence and the remainder of his previous sentence.

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

COUNT 2:

IMPOSED SENTENCE of: 

200 DAYS HUBER with release for work search, work, and AODA treatment/counseling (Concurrent to defendant's other sentence);
**COURT ORDERS THAT THE SENTENCE BE SERVED AT WAUKESHA CO. HUBER - COURT ALSO WAIVES 1/2 OF HUBER FEES**

COURT COSTS:  $253.00 (Includes DRGOD surcharge - to be paid with in 1 year of release from the current sentence);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid with in 1 year of release from the current sentence);
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
